	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002133_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p><add place="margintop" rend="right" hand="#hand01">Livingstone, D<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi></add></p><!--headed paper with address--><!--<p rend="center"><placeName>NEWSTEAD ABBEY</placeName>,</p>
<p rend="center">MANSFIELD</p>
<p rend="center">NOTTS.</p>--><!--end of headed paper address-->
<lb/><p rend="right">8 Dec<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> 1864</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>About Dec<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> 56 
<lb/>or January /57 a 
<lb/>lecture was delivered 
<lb/>by <persName>Prof. Owen</persName> on 
<lb/>Ivory in the 
<lb/>rooms of the 
<lb/><placeName>Society of Arts</placeName>
<lb/>and I had the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002133_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'-->
<lb/>pleasure of hearing 
<lb/>it. My impression 
<lb/>is that he said 
<lb/>that the number 
<lb/>of tusks brought 
<lb/>into the market 
<lb/>of the world warranted 
<lb/>the belief that 
<lb/>38 000 elephants 
<lb/>were destroyed 
<lb/>annually. As 
<lb/>you have the 
<lb/>lecture quotably 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002133_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'-->
<lb/>at hand would 
<lb/>you oblige me by 
<lb/>saying if my 
<lb/>impression is 
<lb/>correct and oblige<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>Yours Most Truly</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p><persName>P Le Neve Foster</persName> Esq</p>
			
